ution": [753, 550]}, "title": "Totally NOT a vegan, you guys!", "last_comment_created": 1779973913912, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": true, "comments": 84, "score_up": 683, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsdsEQPn", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 44, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8645087, "raw_content": "... I found a tick on me after working out in the yard. The front yard. It looked like a larval dog tick, which might make sense as we have lots of dog walkers up and down the street. But I find is suspicious that, in this year with all of the fear porn on ticks I find a tick for the first time HERE.\n\nI'm not unfamiliar with ticks. We'd see them sometimes when camping. My great aunt had a resort on a lake in Minnesota, and we always found ticks after visiting the lakeside. But I haven't seen one in decades, and in 20 years in Florida never saw one...\n\nWe've just finished a week-long rain  event, which is very unusual for Northern Virginia (our \"drought\" has been lessened), and rain will bring out ticks. Still...", "author": "nufosmatic", "created": 1779987629078, "profile_picture": "PiN9pDmgR3ja", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Pederella", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "I have lived in Northern Virginia in a house that backs up on woods for thirty years. We have deer, foxes, skunks, racoons, and God knows what else. And I have been out in my front yard and back yard over that time. And for the VERY FIRST TIME EVER...", "last_comment_created": 1779992892027, "content": "<p>... I found a tick on me after working out in the yard. The front yard. It looked like a larval dog tick, which might make sense as we have lots of dog walkers up and down the street. But I find is suspicious that, in this year with all of the fear porn on ticks I find a tick for the first time HERE.</p>\n<p>I'm not unfamiliar with ticks. We'd see them sometimes when camping. My great aunt had a resort on a lake in Minnesota, and we always found ticks after visiting the lakeside. But I haven't seen one in decades, and in 20 years in Florida never saw one...</p>\n<p>We've just finished a week-long rain  event, which is very unusual for Northern Virginia (our &quot;drought&quot; has been lessened), and rain will bring out ticks. Still...</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 17, "score_up": 44, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsdq06gL", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 618, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8643969, "raw_content": "", "author": "TateDemarcus", "created": 1779935412046, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "PM-Melania-feet-pics", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "cdn.5mind.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsdq06gL.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://cdn.5mind.com/uploads/production/K7sP5KR-X5pIbcUpjvTed/image/3sVLnyiZP7yCjqcZgXnnu.png", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media"